  "source": {
    "digest": "2f5871b80671dd5530849665ad73a00d54b4fcf92e51934c8d025aa73769ec4e",
    "text": "-- The round-trip gate for the versioned syntax artifacts: read one artifact\n-- file, decode it into the typed Syntax vocabulary, re-encode, and print the\n-- exact bytes. arg(0) is the artifact path; arg(1) selects the family\n-- (\"tokens\" or \"surface\"). A refusal prints one structured error line.\nimport Syntax.Codec (..)\n\nfn main() =\n  let text = read_file(arg(0))\n  if arg(1) == \"tokens\" then\n    match decode_tokens(text) of\n      Err(e) => println(\"decode error: {codec_error_message(e)}\")\n      Ok(d) => println(encode_tokens(d))\n  else\n    match decode_surface(text) of\n      Err(e) => println(\"decode error: {codec_error_message(e)}\")\n      Ok(d) => println(encode_surface(d))\n"
  },
